casebody.data:
GRACE BARTON v. WILLIAM DUNLAP et al. [No. 99,

October Term, 1930.]

Decided February 13th, 1931. The cause was argued before Bond, C. J., Pattison, Urner, Adkins, Digges, Parke, and Sloan, JJ. Stevenson A. Williams and H. Courtenay Jenifer, with whom was Fred R. Williams on the brief, for the appellant. John S. Young and Charles H. MacNabb, with whom was John D. C. Duncan on the brief, for the appellee.

The opinion was delivered

per Curiam.
